lead_paragraph: Clemson's defense looked ready to take a big step backward after losing eight starters from its No. 1 unit. Coordinator Brent Venables knew, though, his few returnees like linebackers Ben Boulware and B.J. Goodson, would have a huge say in keeping the defense playing at a national championship level.

headline.print_headline: Linebackers Make Strong Argument for Clemson Defense
